=== Career Progression Pathways

*Within 2-3 years:*
- *Analyst/Senior Analyst*: Taking ownership of report sections, leading workstream analysis, beginning client interaction
- *Specialization*: Developing expertise in specific sectors (e.g., technology, healthcare, industrials, consumer) or service lines (vendor due diligence, debt advisory, valuations)

*Within 3-5 years:*
- *Assistant Manager/Manager*: Leading smaller deals independently, managing junior analysts, direct client relationships, developing commercial judgment

For more detailed pathways, see the Senior Analyst and Manager sections below.

*Alternative paths in first 2-3 years:*
- Move to investment banking (Morgan Stanley, UBS, Macquarie Capital) for deal origination and execution rather than due diligence
- Join private equity fund (e.g., Pacific Equity Partners, Adamantem Capital) as analyst
- Move to corporate development team at major corporation (e.g., Wesfarmers, Woolworths, Telstra)
- Transition to management consulting (McKinsey, BCG, Bain, Strategy&)
- Equity research analyst at investment bank or broker
- Continue in audit/assurance track at same firm with transaction experience as differentiator

