== Conclusion

Transaction support roles in accounting firms offer an excellent entry point into M&A and corporate finance, providing hands-on exposure to deal-making with strong technical training, reasonable work-life balance (compared to investment banking), and multiple career progression pathways. The work combines rigorous financial analysis with commercial problem-solving and client interaction, making it ideal for finance graduates seeking to understand how businesses create and measure value in transactions.

For students interested in M&A, corporate finance, or private equity, starting in transaction support provides foundational skills in financial analysis, commercial judgment, and deal execution that translate well to numerous career paths within and beyond professional services.
